{
  "doc_id": "36670",
  "text": "Other related work includes Wang et al. [CITATION_1] , where the relative entropy measure (Kullback-Leibler divergence) is used to find a similarity transformation between two point-sets under rigid transformation. In Jian et al. [CITATION_2] and Roy et al. [CITATION_3] , nonrigid registration is between pairs of data sets using L2 distance on a mixture of Gaussians model of the data sets. Both methods, however, have not been extended to the problem of unbiased simultaneous matching of multiple point-sets being addressed in this paper. Recently, in [CITATION_4] , Glaunes et al. represent points as delta functions and match them using the dual norm in a reproducing kernel Hilbert space. The resulting 3D spatial integral is difficult to compute numerically. Similarly, the JS divergence proposed earlier [CITATION_5] was estimated using the law of large numbers, making it computationally expensive.",
